to the editor does n't it seem from your sept 5 front page article about air traffic gridlock that the billions in dollars lost wasted or thrown around 5 billion lost last year alone and 40 billion to be spent through 2004 with no end in sight that some of that money would go a long way to finance high speed rail from city center to city center for trips out to about 600 miles rail is faster and with a much larger carrying capacity than comparable short haul airline service not only is it faster and more comfortable but also the reduction in load on the now overstrained airports would go a long way toward freeing up capacity for those longer trips that are more feasible by air j c jordan san francisco sept 5 2000

